# Native-HackClub .gitignore
# If you're wondering why this file is so long, it's because
# Vivado generates approximately one file per atom in the universe.

# ─── Simulation outputs ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Waveform dumps — generated, not source. Don't commit these.
# (A .vcd for a 1ms simulation can be 50MB. Don't be that person.)
*.vcd
*.ghw
*.fst
*.lxt
*.lxt2
*.vzt

# Compiled simulation binaries
*.vvp
a.out
sim.out

# ─── Synthesis outputs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Bitfiles — the compiled hardware. Large, binary, regeneratable.
*.bit
*.bin
*.mcs
*.prm

# ─── Vivado project garbage ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Vivado creates a small city of files when you open a project.
# None of them belong in git.
*.runs/
*.cache/
*.hw/
*.ip_user_files/
*.gen/
*.sim/
*.srcs/
*.xpr
*.jou
*.log
*.str
*.debug_probes
.Xil/
vivado_*.backup.jou
vivado_*.backup.log

# ─── Quartus project garbage ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Intel/Altera's answer to Vivado's mess. Different mess, same energy.
*.qpf
*.qsf
*.qdf
db/
incremental_db/
output_files/
simulation/
*.rpt
*.summary
*.done
*.pin
*.pof
*.sof

# ─── ModelSim / QuestaSim ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
work/
transcript
vsim.wlf
*.wlf
modelsim.ini

# ─── OS noise ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# macOS thinks every folder needs a hidden file. It is wrong.
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Windows similarly cannot help itself
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# Linux thumbnails (rare but they exist)
.Trash-*
.nfs*

# ─── Editor configs ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Your editor preferences are yours. Keep them local.
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
\#*\#
.\#*

# ─── Python (if you have any helper scripts) ───────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyo
.env
venv/

# ─── What to KEEP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# In case you have a docs/ folder with generated waveform screenshots:
# (PNGs are fine — they're small and humans can look at them)
!docs/*.png
!docs/*.jpg
!docs/*.svg